<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12045e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12045e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12045e"> 45(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> White Book</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Apr&egrave;s Robert de Torigni, Pierre Le Roy, vingt- neuvi&egrave;me abb&eacute; (1386-1410), brille d&apos;un &eacute;clat incomparable. S&apos;il fut un des grands moines b&acirc;tisseurs du Mont, il partage avec Robert la gloire d&apos;en &ecirc;tre aussi le grand libraire. Il acheta de nombreux volumes et pour classer avec ordre et m&eacute;thode les centaines de titres de propri&eacute;t&eacute; du monast&egrave;re, il r&eacute;digea lui-m&ecirc;me un registre appel&eacute; le Quanandrier ou Papier Rentier, ainsi qu&apos;un autre livre, dit le Livre Blanc, &agrave; cause de la couleur de sa couverture et sur lequel il avait fait transcrire tous les originaux des actes de donation relatifs &agrave; l&apos;abbaye. Ce registre a disparu. <br><font color="green">[After Robert de Torigni, Pierre Le Roy, twenty-ninth abbot (1386-1410), shines with an incomparable light. One of the great monastic builders of the Mont, he shares with Robert the glory of being also its great librarian. He bought numerous volumes and in order to classify the hundred of property titles of the monastery in orderly and methodical fashion, he created himself a register that was called Quanandrier or Rented Paper, with another book that was called <mark>the White book</mark> because of the colour of its cover and in which he had transcribed all the originals of the donations to the abbey. The latter register has disappeared.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 21</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
